prepare a complete physical count of all the LGU’s properties and submit the report in the required form with assigned value;
maintain property cards for each PPE account to facilitate periodic reconciliation;
reconcile noted discrepancies with the accounting records; and
issue Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) for all properties.

We recommended that Management direct the Municipal Accountant to:
ensure that the payee named in the disbursement voucher is the name of the barangay or the designation of the Barangay Treasurer for all transactions representing financial assistance/obligations due to the barangays to warrant the correctness of the issued check;
ensure that all payment to barangay shall be adequately documented and shall be supported with official receipt to establish validity and accountability of the received fund;
strictly adhere to the provisions of P.D. 1445 and relevant rules and regulations; and
require the payees to account for the funds received to forestall the issuance of Notice of Disallowance.

